===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*kaŋ|t=hill, ridge, mountain}} (STEDT, {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), cognate with {{cog|bo|སྒང||ridge; mound}}, {{cog|my|ခင်|t=ridge}}, {{cog|my|အခေါင်|အ'''ခေါင်'''|summit}}, {{cog|lhu|qhɔ³³||mountain}}, {{cog|suv|gɹaŋ³³||mountain}}, Proto-{{w|Tamangic languages|Tamangic}} *''ᴬgaŋ'' ("hill, mountain").

STEDT also proposes cognacy with {{och-l|京|artificial mound, capital}} and {{och-l|鯨|whale}}.

